Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Up 
get /{format}/BoxScore/{gameid}
Box Score (boxScore)

Path parameters

format (required)
Path Parameter — Desired response format. Valid entries are XML or JSON. default: xml
gameid (required)
Path Parameter — The GameID of a Soccer game. GameIDs can be found in the Games API. Valid entries are 702, 1274, etc. default: null

Return type

BoxScore

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

BoxScore
Up 
get /{format}/BoxScores/{date}
Box Scores by Date (boxScoresByDate)

Path parameters

format (required)
Path Parameter — Desired response format. Valid entries are XML or JSON. default: xml
date (required)
Path Parameter — The date of the game(s).
Examples: 2017-02-27, 2017-09-01. default: null

Return type

array[BoxScore]

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Up 
get /{format}/BoxScoresByCompetition/{competition}/{date}
Box Scores by Date by Competition (boxScoresByDateByCompetition)

Path parameters

format (required)
Path Parameter — Desired response format. Valid entries are XML or JSON. default: xml
competition (required)
Path Parameter — An indication of a soccer competition/league. This value can be the CompetitionId or the Competition Key. Possible values include: EPL, 1, MLS, 8, etc. default: null
date (required)
Path Parameter — The date of the game(s).
Examples: 2017-02-27, 2017-09-01. default: null

Return type

array[BoxScore]

Content-Type: application/json

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Up 
get /{format}/BoxScoresDelta/{date}/{minutes}
Box Scores by Date Delta (boxScoresByDateDelta)

Path parameters

format (required)
Path Parameter — Desired response format. Valid entries are XML or JSON. default: xml
date (required)
Path Parameter — The date of the game(s).
Examples: 2017-02-27, 2017-09-01. default: null
minutes (required)
Path Parameter — Only returns player statistics that have changed in the last X minutes. You specify how many minutes in time to go back. Valid entries are: 1, 2 ... all. default: null

Return type

array[BoxScore]

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Up 
get /{format}/BoxScoresDeltaByCompetition/{competition}/{date}/{minutes}
Box Scores Delta by Date by Competition (boxScoresDeltaByDateByCompetition)

Path parameters

format (required)
Path Parameter — Desired response format. Valid entries are XML or JSON. default: xml
competition (required)
Path Parameter — An indication of a soccer competition/league. This value can be the CompetitionId or the Competition Key. Possible values include: EPL, 1, MLS, 8, etc. default: null
date (required)
Path Parameter — The date of the game(s).
Examples: 2017-02-27, 2017-09-01. default: null
minutes (required)
Path Parameter — Only returns player statistics that have changed in the last X minutes. You specify how many minutes in time to go back. Valid entries are: 1, 2 ... all. default: null

Return type

array[BoxScore]

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Up 
get /{format}/CompetitionDetails/{competition}
Competition Fixtures (League Details) (competitionFixturesLeagueDetails)

Path parameters

format (required)
Path Parameter — Desired response format. Valid entries are XML or JSON. default: xml
competition (required)
Path Parameter — An indication of a soccer competition/league. This value can be the CompetitionId or the Competition Key. Possible values include: EPL, 1, MLS, 8, etc. default: null

Return type

CompetitionDetail

Up

format (required)

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Up 
get /{format}/Competitions
Competitions (Leagues) (competitionsLeagues)

Path parameters

format (required)
Path Parameter — Desired response format. Valid entries are XML or JSON. default: xml

Return type

array[Competition]

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Up 
get /{format}/DfsSlatesByDate/{date}
Dfs Slates By Date (dfsSlatesByDate)

Path parameters

format (required)
Path Parameter — Desired response format. Valid entries are XML or JSON. default: null
date (required)
Path Parameter — The date of the game(s).
Examples: 2020-02-18. default: null

Return type

array[DfsSlate]

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
